&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;A little about us…Fleetio is a modern software platform that helps thousands of organizations worldwide manage their fleet operations. Transportation technology is a hot market, and we’re leading the charge with raving fans and new customers signing up every day. We raised $450M in our Series D funding round in March of 2025 and are on an exciting trajectory as a company. Fleetio is also a proud &lt;a href=&quot;https://rubyonrails.org/foundation&quot;&gt;founding member of the Rails Foundation&lt;/a&gt;!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;More about our team and company:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fleetio overview video: &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YoXyXTFWbkg&quot;&gt;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YoXyXTFWbkg&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Our careers page:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fleetio.com/careers&quot;&gt;https://www.fleetio.com/careers&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for an evidence-based, customer-centric, and innovative Product Manager to join our growing product org. As a Growth PM, you will play a key role in our product-led growth and self-serve initiatives within our Product Growth team. This team is focused on identifying where the product can do more to help customers realize value and where that value can translate into durable business growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your goal will be to understand the core value levers of our product and use strong growth instincts to drive activation, adoption, monetization, retention, and expansion. We believe the strongest product-led growth comes from helping customers realize value through thoughtful product experiences, not from forcing growth at the expense of customer trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to the Growth Group Product Manager, you will build growth loops, develop hypotheses, run experiments, and turn insight into product improvements that create value for both customers and the business. You will partner closely with engineering, design, data, marketing, sales, customer success, and other cross-functional teammates to deliver meaningful outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our ideal candidate is curious, proactive, customer-centric, and energized by solving growth problems through product. You have strong product judgment, a bias toward learning, and a demonstrated ability to turn customer insight and data into measurable impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You have experience in product-led growth and self-serve product development, with a strong understanding of funnels, loops, lifecycle optimization, and experimentation. You are comfortable moving between strategy and execution, and you know how to use both quantitative and qualitative inputs to make sound product decisions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are self-sufficient with data, comfortable exploring dashboards and analyzing funnels, and able to use evidence to influence priorities. You are also fluent in modern AI tools and concepts, whether through building AI-powered features or using AI to improve the quality and speed of your work.&lt;/p&gt;
